# Build output and dependencies
node_modules/
theme/assets/dist/

# Self-hosted webfonts.
#
# Karantina, Assistant, Frank Ruhl Libre and IBM Plex Mono are OFL. Redistributing the
# files would mean shipping the licence text with them; `node tools/fonts.mjs` fetches
# them in one command, so there is nothing to gain by committing them.
theme/src/fonts/
theme/assets/fonts/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Everything seeded from hr-design.co.il.
#
# This repository is PUBLIC, and none of this content is ours: 409 product photographs,
# the catalogue text and descriptions, and the composed scene SVGs with their photography
# embedded as base64. Fetching it into a local dev environment is one thing; republishing
# a third party's commercial catalogue and imagery under our own name is another.
#
# Nothing is lost by excluding it — `node tools/seed/fetch.mjs` reproduces the whole seed,
# and the README documents the sequence.
#
# ANCHORED, and that leading slash is load-bearing. Unanchored, `seed/` matches a
# directory named `seed` at ANY depth, so it silently swallowed all 19 scripts in
# `tools/seed/` — including fetch.mjs, the one this very comment tells you to run. The
# repo is public and its README could not be followed from a fresh clone.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/seed/

*.log
